! conclusion:
  Cyber-ants inherit the ‚Äúwhite space‚Äù doctrine: when food + pheromones slump
  below the epsilon bands and novelty is high, anneal tau upward, penalise
  foraging, and gently bias toward pheromone laying or scouting returns.

  + context: You are declaring the white-space heuristic so cyber-ants can mirror Futon2 behavior.
  + IF:
    Observations satisfy the Futon2 `white?` detector ‚Äî food trace, pheromone
    trace, and recent gather are all low, and the ant is off-nest.

  + HOWEVER:
    Without this guard the agents burn ticks circling barren cells, starving the
    colony even when hunger pressure says ‚Äúexploit elsewhere.‚Äù

  + THEN:
    Encode the heuristics currently embedded in `policy/choose-action` as a
    pattern operator: raise G-adjustments for :forage, lower them for :return and
    :pheromone, and stretch tau when the scout sits on empty nest tiles.

  + BECAUSE:
    Futon5 needs the declarative rule (‚Äúwhite space implies scout stance‚Äù) so it
    can flash cyber-ants or future agents with the same homing instinct.

